  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nThe debugger doesn't provide any sort of good messaging about internal reverts.  It would be good to add a system to the debugger whereby it says when the transaction is about to revert and says something about why (if possible).  Doing this might require changing the `n` command to land at the *end* of a source range rather than the beginning; @gnidan has suggested that we could add `N` as a new name for the existing `n` functionality.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.3.7",
